  "local_port": 57312,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are Top 10 worst black Friday disasters?",
  "response": "Black Friday, known for its massive shopping deals and crowded stores, has seen its fair share of disasters and incidents over the years. Here are ten notable Black Friday disasters:\n\n1. **Walmart Shooting, 2017 (Alabama, USA)**:\n   - A man was shot and injured during an altercation at a Walmart store. The incident heightened concerns about safety during the shopping frenzy.\n\n2. **Walmart Stampede, 2008 (New York, USA)**:\n   - A temporary worker, Jdimytai Damour, was trampled to death at a Long Island Walmart when eager shoppers broke through the doors before the store officially opened.\n\n3. **Target Shooting, 2016 (New Jersey, USA)**:\n   - A man fired shots in a Target store, injuring one person. The incident was part of a larger shootout and led to increased security measures in stores.\n\n4. **Cabela's Shooting, 2014 (Alaska, USA)**:\n   - A man shot and killed another man in a dispute over a parking space at a Cabela's store, highlighting the tensions that can arise on Black Friday.\n\n5. **Toys \"R\" Us Pepper Spray Incident, 2011 (California, USA)**:\n   - A woman used pepper spray on fellow shoppers to gain an advantage in grabbing discounted Xbox consoles, resulting in multiple injuries.\n\n6. **Macy's Black Friday Brawl, 2012 (Washington, USA)**:\n   - A large fight broke out at Macy\u2019s in Seattle over discounted towels, reflecting how even smaller items can lead to conflicts during sales.\n\n7. **Best Buy Shooting, 2012 (Florida, USA)**:\n   - A man was shot in the leg during an altercation in the parking lot of a Best Buy store. The incident underscored the dangers that can occur outside stores as well.\n\n8. **Kmart Shooting, 2010 (Virginia, USA)**:\n   - A shooting in a Kmart parking lot resulted from a dispute over a parking space, highlighting how seemingly minor issues can escalate on Black Friday.\n\n9. **Walmart Pepper Spray Incident, 2011 (California, USA)**:\n   - Similar to the Toys \"R\" Us incident, a woman used pepper spray on fellow shoppers at a Walmart in Los Angeles to gain access to discounted electronics.\n\n10. **Sears Parking Lot Shooting, 2016 (Nevada, USA)**:\n    - A man was shot during an attempted robbery in the Sears parking lot, emphasizing the need for heightened security measures in shopping areas during Black Friday sales.\n\nThese incidents serve as somber reminders of the potential dangers associated with Black Friday and highlight the need for better crowd control, security measures, and awareness among shoppers.",
